  ∴ Write the backstory. FIX TIMELINE: construction must end before departure.
    Journey is 80 years. Arrival 2927 means departure ~2847.

-- LLM evaluation (with geography cross-context and timeline fix):

  yield backstory ≡ "Erebus Station traces its origin to the Exodus Compact, formed in the 2780s when Earth's biosphere entered terminal collapse. The generation ship Prometheus was designed from 2790 and constructed between 2810 and 2847 — a 37-year engineering effort involving every remaining industrial nation. Prometheus departed Earth orbit in 2847 carrying 12,000 colonists across 12 habitation decks. After an 80-year voyage, the Prometheus reached Tau Ceti in 2927 — only to find no habitable worlds. The sole candidate was Hades, a gas giant with a hydrogen-rich atmosphere. Chief Engineer Yuki Tanaka proposed a permanent orbital station using Hades's atmosphere for fusion fuel. Erebus Station was built between 2930 and 2955, incorporating sections of the Prometheus hull into the triple-ring torus design. By 3000, the station houses 50,000 souls across three generations born knowing no other home."

  yield key-events ≡ [
    "2780s — Earth biosphere collapse triggers the Exodus Compact",
    "2810-2847 — Construction of generation ship Prometheus (12 habitation decks)",
    "2847 — Prometheus departs Earth orbit with 12,000 colonists",
    "2927 — Arrival at Tau Ceti. No habitable planets. The Disappointment.",
    "2930-2955 — Erebus Station construction in orbit around gas giant Hades",
    "2971 — The Schism: Returnist faction attempted to commandeer Prometheus engines. Failed. 200 casualties. Led to founding of the Keepers."
  ]

  yield founding-era ≡ "The Disappointment (2927) shaped everything. Colonists expected a new Earth and found only a gas giant. The psychological trauma of permanent exile — no planet beneath your feet, ever — drove the culture toward radical self-sufficiency and reverence for the station. 'We are the station and the station is us' became the founding creed. The 12 decks of the Prometheus became the organizational template: even after building Erebus's 6 sectors, governance retained the 12-representative structure as a link to the ship that carried them."

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ backstory spans ≥ 100 years → ✓ (2780s to 3000 = ~220 years)
--   ⊨ length(key-events) ≥ 3 → ✓ (6 events)
--   ⊨ founding-era explains origin → ✓

-- TIMELINE NOW CONSISTENT: 2810-2847 (build) → 2847 (depart) → 2927 (arrive).
-- 2847 + 80 = 2927. ✓

