-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

⊢ culture
  given seed→premise ≡ "A space station in the year 3000..."
  given geography→layout ≡ "Erebus Station is a triple-ring torus, 2km outer diameter..."
  given history→backstory ≡ "Erebus Station traces its origin to the Exodus Compact..."
  yield customs, social-structure, traditions[], taboos[]

  ∴ Design the culture. FIX: Circle of Twelve = 2 reps per 6 sectors (from
    12 Prometheus decks). Ring Walk distance = ~15km.

-- LLM evaluation (with full cross-context and fixes):

  yield customs ≡ "Station culture is shaped by two inescapable facts: everything is recycled, and there is nowhere else to go. Resources are communal by necessity — private property exists only for personal items that fit in a single storage locker. Privacy is scarce; quarters are small (8m² per person), public spaces are shared. Social bonds are intense, forged in the knowledge that every face you see is one you'll see for life. Music and oral storytelling thrive (zero material cost). Physical violence is nearly unknown — in an enclosed system, every injury depletes the whole."

  yield social-structure ≡ "Governed by the Circle of Twelve — two elected representatives per each of the station's 6 sectors, preserving the original structure of the 12 habitation decks aboard the Prometheus. Executive decisions made by the Station Commander (elected every 8 years from among the Twelve). No hereditary authority. All citizens required to serve 2 years in civic duty (maintenance, farming, teaching, or Keeper security). Informal class tension persists: Spine workers (engineers, commanders) carry higher status than Ring workers (farmers, manufacturers), a divide the Circle struggles to bridge."

  yield traditions ≡ [
    "The Naming Day — at age 12, a child chooses their adult name and civic service specialty. Their home sector celebrates with feasting and gifts of handmade tools.",
    "Harvest Festival — quarterly when the Greenway rotates crop cycles. Feasting, music, and low-gravity dancing in the Middle Ring. The only time alcohol is distributed freely.",
    "The Vigil — annual day of silence commemorating Earth and the 80-year voyage. All lights dimmed for 24 hours. Elders share stories of the old world. Children carry small blue orbs representing Earth.",
    "The Ring Walk — coming-of-age tradition: adolescents walk the full circumference of all three rings in one day (~15km). Tests endurance, teaches the station's geography, and bonds the cohort for life."
  ]

  yield taboos ≡ [
    "Wasting water — the gravest social offense. Even spilling a cup draws collective disapproval. 'Water-waster' is the worst insult in station vernacular, worse than any profanity.",
    "Wind talk — speaking of leaving the station or suggesting a better home exists elsewhere. Echoes the Returnist Schism of 2971. Named because 'there is no wind in space' — the desire for an open sky is considered a dangerous delusion.",
    "Hoarding — keeping resources beyond your single-locker allocation. Quarters subject to random community inspections. Punishment: public accounting (your hoard displayed in the Commons) and loss of sector voting rights for one election cycle."
  ]

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ social-structure describes governance → ✓ (Circle of Twelve, 2 per sector)
--   ⊨ length(traditions) ≥ 3 → ✓ (4)
--   ⊨ length(taboos) ≥ 2 → ✓ (3)
--   ⊨ customs reflect enclosed space life → ✓

